\\\\n- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Correctness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation of R11 Call-Response Gating correctly transforms the follower's phrase shape based on the leader's realized performance. The logic in `_descend_from_apex` and `_fill` accurately reflects the requirements for complementarity and filling. Specifically:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- When the leader is building (`is_building=True`), the follower's amplitude is reduced and its contour apex is inverted to complement the leader.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- When the leader is pausing (`is_pausing=True`), the follower's amplitude is boosted and its contour apex is reinforced to fill the gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Role metadata (`leader`, `follower`, `solo`, `tacet`) is correctly parsed and respected, with the rule only applying to voices explicitly tagged as followers.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe task is complete according to the acceptance criteria:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation is consistent with other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tier 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, 